The portion before the &#39;@&#39; in the authority is &#39;userinfo&#39;,
which in HTTP is used for authentication. So,
  http://david@.../
would result in a host header
  Host: ascher.com
and a challenge to the user for the password for &#39;david&#39;.

Cheers,



